{"word":"μονάς","slug":"μονάς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μονάς</b></el> <el>(μονάς, <el>ionic</el> <el>μουνάς, άδος</el>,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>special <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:μόνος'><el>μόνος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>alone, solitary</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; as <a href='S:masculine'>masc.</a> of a man, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>μονάς, άδος</el>, <i>a unit</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}